DRDGold Slides in Johannesburg After Saying Quarterly Production Will Drop

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-04-06T07:18:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/drdgold-slides-in-johannesburg-after-saying-quarterly-production-will-drop.html
DRDGold Ltd. (DRD)  fell in opening trading
in Johannesburg after the gold miner said production for the
three months to March 31 is expected to be about 3 percent lower
than the previous quarter.  Shares in the company fell 3 cents, or 0.8 percent, to 3.55
rand as of 9:16 a.m., curbing the advance so far this year to
4.7 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  